        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Mattermost open DM validation",
        "body": "## Summary\n- reject Mattermost `dmPolicy=\"open\"` without wildcard `allowFrom` in config validation\n- surface the same misconfiguration in Mattermost channel status\n- include DM drop reason/hint in Mattermost monitor logs\n\n## Root Cause\nMattermost's Zod schema already required the wildcard, but the CLI validation path validates generated JSON Schema metadata, which loses `superRefine` dependency checks. The runtime then blocked DMs as not allowlisted, but logs/status did not explain the missing wildcard.\n\n## Tests\n- `pnpm test extensions/mattermost/src/status-issues.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor-auth.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.authz.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/channel-actions-setup-status.contract.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/config-schema.test.ts src/config/validation.channel-metadata.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/mattermost/src/status-issues.ts extensions/mattermost/src/status-issues.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/channel.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor-auth.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor-auth.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/config-schema.test.ts src/config/validation.ts src/config/validation.channel-metadata.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- temp `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` bad Mattermost config with `pnpm openclaw config validate --json` rejects `channels.mattermost.allowFrom`",
